The paper deals with the security aspects of distributed storage systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of regenerating codes and cooperative repair mechanisms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The analysis of storage systems and the use of graph representations suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-fields of systems and networking (cs.SI) and computer communication (cs.CC).
